<section>
    <h2>Tips for Buyers</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Verify the Seller: Check their profile, feedback, and transaction history.</li>
        <li>Use Secure Payment Methods: Avoid direct transfers. Use platforms with buyer protection.</li>
        <li>Avoid Personal Information Sharing: Never share personal or financial details.</li>
        <li>Research the Item: Know the value and authenticity of the item you're buying.</li>
        <li>Avoid Suspicious Links: Do not click on unknown links or download files from untrusted sources.</li>
        <li>Be Wary of Too-Good-To-Be-True Offers: Extremely low prices may be a red flag.</li>
        <li>Communicate within the Platform: Use the platform's messaging system rather than personal contact information.</li>
        <li>Report Suspicious Activity: Report any suspicious behavior to the platform administrators.</li>
        <li>Keep Records: Save all communications and transaction details.</li>
        <li>Check Reviews: Read reviews and ratings from other users.</li>
        <li>Ask Questions: Donâ€™t hesitate to ask the seller detailed questions about the item.</li>
        <li>Trust Your Instincts: If something feels off, it probably is.</li>
        <li>Use Official Channels: Only use official websites and apps for transactions.</li>
        <li>Avoid Upfront Payments: Be cautious of requests for payment before receiving the item.</li>
        <li>Double-Check Details: Verify the item details and payment information before completing a transaction.</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Tips for Sellers</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Verify the Buyer: Check their profile and feedback history.</li>
        <li>Use Secure Payment Methods: Avoid direct transfers. Use platforms with seller protection.</li>
        <li>Avoid Personal Information Sharing: Never share personal or financial details.</li>
        <li>Meet in Secure Locations: If meeting in person, choose public, well-lit areas.</li>
        <li>Avoid Suspicious Links: Do not click on unknown links or download files from untrusted sources.</li>
        <li>Be Wary of Too-Good-To-Be-True Offers: Extremely high offers may be a red flag.</li>
        <li>Communicate within the Platform: Use the platform's messaging system rather than personal contact information.</li>
        <li>Report Suspicious Activity: Report any suspicious behavior to the platform administrators.</li>
        <li>Keep Records: Save all communications and transaction details.</li>
        <li>Use Official Channels: Only use official websites and apps for transactions.</li>
        <li>Educate Yourself: Stay informed about common scams and how to recognize them.</li>
        <li>Check Reviews: Read reviews and ratings from other users.</li>
        <li>Ask Questions: Donâ€™t hesitate to ask the buyer detailed questions about their intentions.</li>
        <li>Trust Your Instincts: If something feels off, it probably is.</li>
        <li>Avoid Rush Transactions: Scammers often create a sense of urgency.</li>
        <li>Secure Your Accounts: Use strong, unique passwords and enable two-factor authentication.</li>
        <li>Escrow Services: Consider using an escrow service for high-value transactions.</li>
        <li>Double-Check Details: Verify the buyerâ€™s details and payment information before completing a transaction.</li>
        <li>Use Shipping with Tracking: Always use a shipping method that provides tracking information.</li>
        <li>Require Confirmation of Receipt: Request that the buyer confirms receipt of the item to avoid disputes.</li>
    </ul>
